name: Shipping Forecast Regions Poster
description:
The Shipping Forecast was first broadcast in the 1920s its intended objective was to warn seafarers of impending storms and gales. Its solemn, rhythmic tones has inspired poems, songs, novels and artists. As familiar though the sea areas are by name, few of us give much thought to where they are.

Designed by myself and professionally printed in the UK on A3 (297 x 420mm) this contemporary print shows the shipping areas in a modern and graphic style; printed on high quality 180gsm paper in matt finish; this print is bound to be a conversation starter.

Poster comes unframed as standard.
Framed option available: Handmade frame by Uckfield Framing Company in Sussex, using sustainable wood moulding, with attractive raised grain and white wash finish. Safely glazed with 2mm styrene, it is ready to hang straight on your wall. Overall frame size is 345 x 468mm. 

All of my prints can be custom ordered to A4, A3, A2, A1 or A0. Please email me for details.

If you have any questions regarding this product simply drop me a line and i'd be happy to help.

name: Mt. Kilimanjaro Charity Print - customisable
description:
Mt. Kilimanjaro is the highest free standing mountain in the world at 5,895 metres above sea level and one of Africa's most iconic landmarks.
As a keen lover of the outdoors I am due to summit Mt. Kilimanjaro on New Years Day 2014. My training has included meeting so many interesting and different people with the same dream, to push themselves mentally and physically and climb this epic mountain. Their determination has inspired this print!

Available as a generic print OR customise it... are you climbing? have climbed? or know someone who has climbed? Have their name and date of summit put onto this print as an ever lasting reminder of their fantastic achievement.

I am climbing Kilimanjaro for 2 charities who are really close to my heart: Macmillan Cancer Support and Epilepsy Research UK. 20% of all profit from sales of this print will go to my fundraising for these charities.

Designed by myself and professionally printed in the UK on A3 (297 x 420mm) this contemporary print shows Mt. Kilimanjaro in a modern and graphic style; printed on high quality 180gsm paper in matt finish; this print is bound to be a conversation starter.

Poster comes unframed as standard.
Framed option available: Handmade frame by Uckfield Framing Company in Sussex, using sustainable wood moulding, with attractive raised grain and white wash finish. Safely glazed with 2mm styrene, it is ready to hang straight on your wall. Overall frame size is 345 x 468mm.

name: Uganda Portrait Charity print For Many Ogilvy Hands by Guest Artist
description:
Many Ogilvy Hands is a charity set up by advertising agency Ogilvy & Mather in conjunction with International Needs. Together they support the building of primary and secondary schools in Buikwe, Uganda.

For the last five years O&M has been supporting trips three times a years for employees to get their hands dirty and help with the building and experience first hand how the money raised by this amazing charity directly helps, offering kids not only the possibility to learn but also to engage with each other, be creative, safe and part of a community. Somewhere they can call their own.

This year I (James Dean) am lucky enough to be going and as well as part of my initial fundraising, these prints represent my on-going commitment to raising money and supporting MOH long after my trip is completed. All profit will go to the Many Ogilvy Hands Charity.

Designed by myself, James Dean and professionally printed in the UK on A3 (297 x 420mm); printed on high quality 180gsm paper in matt finish; this print is bound to be a conversation starter.

Poster comes unframed. 
This print can be custom ordered to A4 or A3. Please email me for details.

If you have any questions regarding this product simply drop me a line and i'd be happy to help.
